#################################################################
#    Classes
#################################################################

###  http://dbpedia.org/resource/Category:Relevance_fallacies
<http://dbpedia.org/resource/Category:Relevance_fallacies> rdf:type owl:Class ;
    rdfs:label "Relevance_fallacies" ;
    rdfs:comment "Relevance fallacies are errors in reasoning where the premise is irrelevant to the conclusion." .

###  http://dbpedia.org/resource/Whataboutism
<http://dbpedia.org/resource/Whataboutism> rdf:type owl:Class ;
    rdfs:label "Whataboutism" ;
    rdfs:comment "Whataboutism, also known as whataboutery, is a logical fallacy that attempts to discredit an opponent's position by charging them with hypocrisy without directly refuting or disproving their argument." .

###  http://dbpedia.org/resource/Confirmation_bias
<http://dbpedia.org/resource/Confirmation_bias> rdf:type owl:Class ;
    rdfs:label "Confirmation_bias" ;
    rdfs:comment "Confirmation bias is the tendency to search for, interpret, favor, and recall information in a way that confirms one's preexisting beliefs or theories." .
